After Wang Xuesong left his "highly sensitive" e a car in the service area, he couldn't figure out: "Is a person an infectious agent, or is a car an infectious agent? "

This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Li Muyan, southern weekend correspondent

By Chen Yajie, southern weekend staff writer

Editor in chief

In the past month, Xiao Hongbing, a 50-year-old truck driver, has driven his light truck halfway across China. On January 7,2020, he set off from Jingzhou, Zhejiang, Guizhou, Hunan, Guangdong, Fujian, near the New Year's Eve emergency orders, more than 200 yuan, and his family an account, gritted his teeth and then turned to run to Sichuan.

On the way, I had to navigate on my phone, so I didn't have time to watch the news. On the first day of the New Year, when he hit the highway, something didn't feel right, as if the freeway was full of cops, wearing protective clothing, a mask, someone taking his temperature. He's never seen anything like it.

The truck stopped at a small town in Sichuan to unload the goods, and several locals kept a long eye on him. A little while later came the police car, asked Xiao Hongbing to take his temperature, check his previous itinerary. He learned that his hometown of Hubei has become an epidemic area, many places do not allow foreign vehicles to enter, his Hubei license plate is the focus of attention.

The police asked him to leave as soon as possible. Later, when he was resting and eating at another place, locals surrounded his van with tricycles and called the police. Everywhere he went, Xiao explained to people that he hadn't been to Hubei since early January, but it didn't help much. People just said, hurry up and don't infect us with Hubei's diseases. Whether you are sick or not, you'd better not come to us.

Xiao Hongbing had to go on the high-speed, began to stray. Unwilling to go home empty, he continued to try to pick up orders, want to go to Shaanxi pull rice, halfway, the other side said Hubei car can not come in, the business is yellow again. He walked through national roads, rural roads, the middle of the night through the winding mountain road, everywhere not to allow foreign vehicles through. Later, the service area did not let him stop, urged him to go quickly, Xiao Hongbing completely no place to rest and sleep.

When he is really sleepy, he slaps his face and plucks his hair. Wandered around for over a week, almost hit the high-speed rail, ran in the wrong direction at one point.

On the afternoon of January 29, traffic police on duty in Hanzhong, Shaanxi Province, patrolled a highway and found a car parked in the emergency lane. The driver fell asleep. They knocked on the window, Xiao Hongbing woke up, he said, "I'm too tired, too tired, " and cried.

After 22 days away from home, Xiao finally stopped at a service area north of Hanzhong. Traffic police for his temperature, buy fruit, arranged him on-site isolation, but he was afraid to pay the hotel money, did not dare to ask the price, refused. These days of gas and tolls cost him half a month's income. In the service area, he still sleeps in the car.

After another ten days or so, he was reported by the media, constantly strangers call, comfort him, for his donations, the money soon exceeded 10,000, Xiao Hongbing quickly announced that no longer accept. The cell phone was called to no electricity, Xiao Hongbing kept saying thank you to people. On the night of his interview with southern weekend, he still didn't make it home, but he was lucky enough to get a free dorm room in the service area.

There are no specific statistics on how many people are stranded on the roads. A number of provinces and cities have implemented traffic controls that only allow people to go in and out. Many toll booths have been closed and closed. On February 7, the Shandong provincial government announced that it had persuaded 615 vehicles from other provinces to return.

On "Douyin, " someone broadcast his tortuous journey from Yunnan to Zhejiang and back again, running eight tanks of oil and gaining more than 40,000 fans.

Nimana, a vineyard farmer, wanted to return to Xiangyang after spending the New Year in his hometown of Guizhou. He had passed the quarantine period and heard that Xiangyang was not closed to the city, so he drove on. Did Not expect to pass through Chongqing, not let go, asked "where to go back from" . "I won't get off from you. I'm not even allowed to pass through here. " He felt helpless.

The southern weekend reporter interviewed many car owners have experienced a dilemma: The destination does not let in, the departure does not let back. The phrase they hear most often is, go back to where you came from.

1
"Go back tomorrow. "

1

###"Go back tomorrow. "

Chen Qin slept in the car for 14 days. The armrests pressed against his ribs when the seat was flat, and lying on his side was uncomfortable and still painful. He drove to Jiangxi years ago to see friends. When the epidemic broke out, he couldn't get into the village. He bought a quilt. I can't believe it took 14 days.

At first he drove around looking for food, parked at the edge of different villages, place can not be too conspicuous, stop for a while will be someone to take photos, report. His "Zhejiang c" license plate became sensitive as the disease in Wenzhou intensified.

A pair of GRANDPA and grandma selling fried rice noodles to see him poor, want to secretly invite him to live at home, but the son did not agree. She winked at him, told him not to talk, and hurried away after buying. The village ordered her not to sell to anyone who spoke Mandarin.

Chen Qin put fried rice noodles into the car "like a thief to eat. ". For many days he had nothing but instant noodles and no hot water. He had to gnaw on them, his mouth dry to the point of bleeding.

On the eighth day of the Lunar New Year, the police knocked on the window to receive a report from the crowd and asked him to leave. Chen Qin drove around, in front of the church to find a piece of treasure, "this is observed around ten miles, but not out of the safe zone of the best location. ". The downside is that when night falls, there's a graveyard nearby, and if you leave the lights on, there's a reflection out the window, like someone's lying around looking at him. He's afraid to turn off the engine, but he's afraid of running out of gas.

During the day, he spent most of the time in his car, afraid to open the windows wide, afraid of viruses. He watched the news and movies about the epidemic, fell asleep repeatedly and was so bored that he went for a walk in the nearby mountains.

Chen Qin thought of his year enough bad luck, business failure, with debt, no face to go back to Anhui home for the New Year, his wife and daughter in Sichuan. Several of his restaurants in Wenzhou had closed for the day, and he wanted to get away before he ran out.

He sometimes sends out a FRIEND CIRCLE TO COMFORT HIMSELF: "Life is not so perfect, at least still alive. "

The good people of the church opened the door for him to supply electricity, Chen Qin secretly went to the supermarket to buy rice cookers, rice and pickled mustard tuber, have not had time to use, and was reported. The police took him to a nearby health centre where he had a medical examination and the director gave him a certificate of good health. They took him to the Shangrao Highway and said, "if you go back this time, don't come back. " .

On the highway, Chen Qin do not know where to drive. For a long time without a car, he ran alone on the highway. He went to refuel, the oil gun for a long time can not squeeze oil, staff said for many days no one to come, the machine is broken.

This scene, Jiangxi People Wang Xuesong also saw. After spending time in Wuhan a few years ago, he drove a car from Hubei, although he hadn't been to Hubei in a long time. He was afraid of being seen when he passed the gas station.

Wang Xuesong set out at night and hurried back to work in Shanghai. He drove to Kaihua, Zhejiang Province, where he was not allowed to pass. He had to double back and return to Jiangxi, where the toll gate he had passed six hours earlier was closed. He described himself as "particularly heartbroken" as his family's toll booth refused to check his identity card, driving records or Wuhan license plates and refused to let him back in.

Turning back for more than 300 kilometers, Wang Xuesong arrived in Longgang, Zhejiang, at six o'clock in the morning. Though he could not get through, the traffic police led him to the service area for a rest. He slept off and on for two hours in the car.

He hid himself in the Mount Sanqing service area, the only place of business he could find along the way. He asked the person in charge of the service area if he had a place to stay. He could pay, but the other person said No. Ask anyone. Either you're too scared to touch him, or you don't know. A cleaning Lady's wife snuck him into the workshop to use the rice cooker. Porridge cooked, Chen Qin went to the supermarket to buy a pot of eight treasure porridge, with the inside of the spoon to drink porridge. Big Brother got him a fish from the canteen.

The clothes he had brought out were wet and smelly. Big Brother took him to the laundry room. At night, while everyone was sleeping, Chen Qin secretly washed the clothes. After airing it out, there was a heavy rain, all soaked and washed again. Chen Qin bought an umbrella again and covered his clothes.

He was so grateful that he wanted to cry. He took the Moutai from his car, but big brother refused to take it. At night, he still sleeps in his car. I don't fall asleep until after 3:00 every day, and I wake up at 8:00 in the morning. Chen Qin every day is thinking: "tomorrow go back, go back tomorrow, go back tomorrow" .

2
"are people infected, or are cars infected? "

2

###"are people infected, or are cars infected? "

Wake up, Wang Xuesong found trapped in the service area of four or five private cars, two car owners have disappeared. Everyone is Hubei brand, the longest has been stranded for four days, do not know how to do, "the only consensus is to wait. ".

They called every help they could think of. The mayor's hotline told them to coordinate with the highway traffic police; they couldn't; they called the media and 110, all to no avail. They asked if they could leave the car in the service area, and the feedback was no. But we still do, a car owner to find a friend to pick them up from Hangzhou, a few "share weal and woe" strangers, finally together in this car fled the highway.

The car was dropped off, and the man made it through. After Wang Xuesong left his "highly sensitive" e-a car in the service area, he couldn't understand this: "is a person infected or is a car infected? "

A Very Tight Place, a family of four from Anhui Province, spent a day and a night running back and forth on the highway. The Hubei identity cards of the husband and two children have been a big problem, although they have not been back to Hubei this year.

A little after 2:00 in the morning, before the highway junction in Anhui's hometown, the traffic police discussed with them whether they could get the community to open a marriage certificate to prove the identity of the husband. Family is on the way, the notice came again: or not, "No matter what documents you are out of line. ".

Qi Min and her husband took turns driving the car. They didn't know where to go. They can only get 100 yuan in gas. They keep on driving, keep on driving. Her seven-year-old son asked her, "I regret that I am from Hubei. "

Finally they decided to leave the car on the highway and walk home. The family of four climbed over the fence at dawn and crossed the mountain path with a flashlight.

Chen Qin, who had been holed up in a Mount Sanqing service area for a few days, felt he had to leave anyway. His blood sugar was low, he was dizzy, he drank a can of coffee and headed off to Wenzhou to try a few highways one by one. After running all day and trying the third one, he finally succeeded in running through the pass in the east of Wenzhou.

It had been dark, in the national road happily ran for a while, found that bayonet is still a lot. After a bridge, Chen Qin was again stopped, asked to turn back. His experience has been hot on the Internet, traffic police recognized him, Chen Qin begged them, he has not eaten a day, his heart rate accelerated, it can not walk. The traffic policeman made him a bowl of instant noodles and brought him oranges.

Traffic police and higher coordination said, the local people came to vouch for him, to take him back to the county. Only 35 minutes from the county seat, Chen Qin feel almost in sight. Friends put him in touch with each other for half an hour, but nothing came of it. Chen Qin broke down and pulled over to the side of the road to cry.

Fortunately, in view of his special circumstances, he was in Yongjia County at the time, "in extraordinary circumstances" -- in lock-up. On the 15th day, Chen finally checked into a hotel with a bed, hot water and a Three Meals a Day to the door for 2,000 yuan in 14 days. The first thing he did after landing at 11 am was take a hot bath.

During these days of detention, friends gave Chen Qin a lot of advice, the worst case plan is to leave the car, alone out of the highway. People are always okay.

But leaving the car behind can cost you a lot of high-speed overtime, charged by the hour. Wang Xuesong and Qi Min are worried about their cars, do not know when to get back, will have been reported towed away.

Chen Qin's secret is also money: He is afraid of being charged overtime fees, as well as the cost of isolation after the next. Because of money, he did not dare to go home for the New Year, nor did he dare to contact his wife and daughter. He was in debt to his brother, who thought that being away was his punishment.

The trip cost him 1,500 yuan in gas money, equivalent to a month's rent in Wenzhou. When he was stuck on the road, the credit company gave him an ultimatum to notify his friends and family in his address book. With only $13.89 left in his card, he filled the tank after a friend called with some money.

Chen Qin has not been able to return home, even if it is useless to return. He doesn't know when the epidemic will end, restaurants will be closed, staff will still be trapped in their dormitories, and his business will collapse. He told southern weekend that the trip was nothing and that "more painful things are yet to come" .

(Chen Qin, Wang Xuesong and Qi Min are aliases, thanks to Wei Yingjie and Lu Fei for their help in this article.)
